  "issue_title": "label_multiplier reads last LABELED_EVENT instead of current labels",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\n`PullRequest.from_graphql_response` in `gittensor/classes.py:300-303` reads the PR's label from the chronologically-last `LABELED_EVENT` timeline item. When a PR has multiple labels or a label is later removed, the validator picks the wrong one and applies the wrong `label_multiplier`.\n\nAfter PR #545 introduced the 0.5\u00d7 penalty for `refactor`/`cleanup`/`chore`, this bypasses the penalty whenever a maintainer adds a workflow label (`lgtm`, `blocked`, `size:*`, `topic:*`) after the scoring label.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Open [entrius/gittensor-ui#313](https://github.com/entrius/gittensor-ui/pull/313). Maintainer @anderdc applied `feature` \u2192 removed \u2192 `enhancement` \u2192 `blocked` \u2192 removed. Current labels: `[enhancement]`.\n2. Check the [gittensor.io scorecard](https://gittensor.io/miners/pr?repo=entrius%2Fgittensor-ui&number=313) \u2014 it shows `Label (blocked) 1.00x`.\n3. `blocked` is not applied to the PR and isn't in `LABEL_MULTIPLIERS`; `enhancement` is applied and maps to `1.10\u00d7`.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\n`label_multiplier` reflects a label that is still currently applied to the PR.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`label_multiplier` is derived from whichever label was added last \u2014 even if later removed or never in `LABEL_MULTIPLIERS`. PR #313 gets `1.00\u00d7` instead of `1.10\u00d7`.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Linux\n- Python version: 3.12\n- Commit/Version: `test` branch @ `10c5cd6`\n\n## Additional Context\n\nDistinct from #536 / PR #553 (null `label` from repo-deleted labels). This bug is about valid current labels being masked.\n\n**Suggested fix:** add the PR's `labels` connection to the GraphQL query and pick the last LABELED_EVENT whose label is both still currently applied and in `LABEL_MULTIPLIERS`.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-20T23:52:57.000Z",
